President Barack Obama has proclaimed September 18-24, 2016, as National Farm Safety and Health Week. This proclamation acknowledges the important role that farmers and ranchers play in our economy and recognizes the risks they face in their daily work. The proclamation emphasizes the need to provide farmers with the necessary tools, training, and resources to ensure their safety and well-being. It also encourages increased awareness of proper safety procedures and the implementation of youth farm safety education programs. The proclamation calls upon agencies, organizations, businesses, and extension services to strengthen their commitment to promoting farm safety and health programs. Finally, President Obama urges Americans to honor and appreciate the contributions of farmers, ranchers, and farmworkers to our nation.